    "text": "By Dustin Massengill ,\n2 hours ago\nLEXINGTON, Ky. ( FOX 56 ) — A fugitive murder suspect from Alabama has been caught in Kentucky.\nThe U.S. Marshals Service contacted Lexington police Thursday, saying a man wanted for murder in Alabama may be headed to Lexington.\nLATEST KENTUCKY NEWS: Alabama fugitive wanted on murder charge arrested at Lexington hotel Bullitt County mother who shot, killed sons sentenced New faces join Kentucky leadership, including full slate of House Democrats Police said they were able to use flock cameras and track down the vehicle at the Comfort Inn on Buena Vista Road.\nThere they arrested 30-year-old Kiarah Jones.\nHe was lodged in the Fayette County Detention Center as a fugitive from another state on charges of murder and possession of a controlled substance.\nCopyright 2024 Nexstar Media, Inc. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed. For the latest news, weather, sports, and streaming video, head to FOX 56 News.",
